quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  28,71,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúImagine if God were to make the night perpetual for you until the Day of Judgment, which god other than God could bring you sunlight? Will you not then listen?‚ÄĚ"
  28,72,"Ask ňĻthem alsoňļ, ‚ÄúImagine if God were to make the day perpetual for you until the Day of Judgment, which god other than God could bring you night to rest in? Will you not then see?‚ÄĚ"
  28,73,"It is out of His mercy that He has made for you the day and night so that you may rest ňĻin the latterňļ and seek His bounty ňĻin the formerňļ, and perhaps you will be grateful"
  28,74,"And ňĻwatch forňļ the Day He will call to them, ‚ÄúWhere are those you claimed were My associate-gods?‚ÄĚ"
  28,75,"And We will bring forth a witness¬†from every faith-community and ask ňĻthe polytheistsňļ, ‚ÄúShow ňĻUsňļ your proof.‚ÄĚ Then they will ňĻcome toňļ know that the truth is with God ňĻaloneňļ. And whatever ňĻgodsňļ they fabricated will fail them"
  28,76,"Indeed, Korah¬†was from the people of Moses, but he behaved arrogantly towards them. We had granted him such treasures that even their keys would burden a group of strong men. ňĻSome ofňļ his people advised him, ‚ÄúDo not be prideful! Surely God does not like the prideful"
  28,77,"Rather, seek the ňĻrewardňļ of the Hereafter by means of what God has granted you, without forgetting your share of this world. And be good ňĻto othersňļ as God has been good to you. Do not seek to spread corruption in the land, for God certainly does not like the corruptors.‚ÄĚ"
